    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions About Mushroom Gummies for Immune Support</h2>
    <details class="fq"><summary>How do mushrooms support the immune system?</summary><p>Beta-glucans bind Dectin-1 and CR3 receptors on immune cells, activating macrophages, NK cells, and dendritic cells. This trains/primes the immune system for more effective pathogen response — immunomodulation, not overstimulation. Turkey tail and reishi have the strongest evidence.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Which mushroom is best for immunity?</summary><p>Turkey tail (#1): PSK/PSP approved as adjunct immune therapy in Japan, 400+ studies. Reishi (#2): triterpenes + polysaccharides for immune modulation + stress/sleep. Chaga: antioxidant immune cell protection. Maitake: D-fraction macrophage activation. Best: turkey tail + reishi combined.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>What are beta-glucans and why do they matter?</summary><p>Complex polysaccharides in mushroom cell walls that activate immune receptors. The primary immune-active compounds. Products need 20%+ verified beta-glucans for meaningful effect. Many products are mostly grain starch with low beta-glucans. Always check verification.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Can I take mushroom immune gummies every day?</summary><p>Yes. Clinical trials support up to 6 months daily use. Traditional Asian medicine uses mushrooms daily for millennia. Beta-glucans modulate rather than overstimulate immunity — safe for daily use. Year-round supplementation maintains sustained immune readiness.</p></details>
    <details class="fq"><summary>Turkey tail vs. reishi: which is better for immune support?</summary><p>Turkey tail: strongest direct immune activator (PSK/PSP, NK cells, macrophages). Reishi: best immune modulator + stress/sleep support (which affects immunity). Combining both is ideal: turkey tail for direct activation + reishi for modulation and stress-immune support.</p></details>

